<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1193]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,334,877,902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Discussion.</emphasis>
.This new species shows similarity with 
<taxonomicName box="[802,979,878,902]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leehelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvicapsula" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[802,979,878,902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">L. parvicapsula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[987,1042,878,902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[987,1042,878,902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in number of spines on hind tibial comb but differs in dark narrow band on hind tibiae. The species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Tokunaga" authorityName="Tokunaga" box="[1002,1298,913,937]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Homohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hollandiensis">
<emphasis box="[1002,1181,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">L. hollandiensis</emphasis>
Tokunaga
</taxonomicName>
in pale palp segments, color of basal and distal flagellomeres, scutum with dark brown caudolateral and lateral areas, pale wing membrane and brown anterior veins. Scutellar bristles and brown abdominal tergites with dark laterad of 
<taxonomicName authority="Debenham" authorityName="Debenham" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leehelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasseli">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,985,1009]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">L. wasseli</emphasis>
Debenham
</taxonomicName>
look like those of the present species. The following combination of characters: pale trochanter, color pattern of femur and tibia, structure and 
